1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:13,533
<i> I don't know how to thank you.</i>

2
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:16,200
<i>I'll testify against Hazel Cruz</i>

3
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:17,600
<i> if you decide to file a case.</i>

4
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:18,500
<i> You shameless people!</i>

5
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:19,933
<i> You have no shame! Huh?</i>

6
00:00:20,067 --> 00:00:21,733
<i> I'll sue you, understand?</i>

7
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:23,200
<i> I'll sue both of you!</i>

8
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:26,233
<i>Can you stay in Davao
for just two days?</i>

9
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:28,533
<i>It's almost the weekend anyway.</i>

10
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:29,867
<i> Book me a ticket.</i>

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,267
<i>I'll go with you
to Davao tonight.</i>

12
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,533
<i>- Dad.
- Jeff.</i>

13
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:45,567
- Is this okay?
- Yes.

14
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,500
So, Dad?

15
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:48,033
Are you excited
to surprise Mom?

16
00:00:48,167 --> 00:00:49,533
Very excited, son.

17
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:50,867
Very, very excited.

18
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:55,000
- I'll take care of it.
- Okay, there.

19
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:14,300
Are you sure you're coming
with me to Davao?

20
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:17,067
Oh, what kind of question
is that, Sir Noah?

21
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,167
You can see
she's already packing.

22
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,333
What I mean is...
the kids.

23
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:24,833
How would you explain it
to them?

24
00:01:24,967 --> 00:01:26,067
Didang will handle that.

25
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:26,833
Oh, wait.

26
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:28,467
Ma'm, why me?

27
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,633
I just haven't thought
of an excuse yet.

28
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:35,600
Felma, why do you want to come
with me to Davao?

29
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:39,267
For a second opinion.

30
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:41,967
Don't make your cousin
come here.

31
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:43,933
I'll go to him myself.

32
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:46,033
Ma'am, is that really
the reason?

33
00:01:46,167 --> 00:01:48,600
All right, I support you.

34
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:51,500
I'll explain it to the kids.

35
00:01:51,633 --> 00:01:54,100
But is it okay if I tell them

36
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:56,867
you're checking out
a business in Davao?

37
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,567
That's up to you.

38
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:00,967
What about Manuel?

39
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:04,400
How do you think he will react?

40
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,033
Oh my god!

41
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:07,033
I didn't think about that.

42
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:09,100
Ma'am, he'll get jealous...

43
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:11,867
Why?

44
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,900
We're not together anymore.

45
00:02:14,067 --> 00:02:15,300
But you still love
each other, Ma'am.

46
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:16,667
Didang!

47
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,633
He's with Hazel now.

48
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:23,633
We don't have the right
to be jealous anymore.

49
00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:34,600
Attorney, they're falsely
accusing me.

50
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:38,367
They're blaming me
for something I didn't do.

51
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,533
You're the one who ordered us!

52
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:43,333
You told us to harass Miss Becca
and her grandchildren.

53
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:45,067
What are you talking about?

54
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,033
Why would I do that?

55
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,567
Wait.

56
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:51,200
Who is this Miss Becca
you're talking about?

57
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:52,600
We don't even know her.

58
00:02:52,733 --> 00:02:55,767
That woman told us to scare her

59
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,367
and burn down her house.

60
00:02:58,767 --> 00:03:00,433
The nerve of this man.

61
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:04,233
Attorney,
the only Becca I know...

62
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:06,133
is Timo's mother.

63
00:03:06,267 --> 00:03:08,267
And I don't have any issue
with her.

64
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,300
So why would I do that?

65
00:03:10,433 --> 00:03:12,267
Besides, Timo is already
in jail, right?

66
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,833
I get it now.

67
00:03:16,967 --> 00:03:19,433
You're the ones who have
a grudge against me.

68
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:20,867
What?

69
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:23,333
You're doing this
to get back at me?

70
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:24,900
What?

71
00:03:25,033 --> 00:03:26,700
Oh, right?

72
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:28,600
Maybe you think
I already forgot.

73
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:32,233
When you were working
at Southcrest, I caught you.

74
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:34,067
Stealing patients' medicines.

75
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,700
And then what?

76
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:37,367
You sold them outside.

77
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:38,600
Didn't you?

78
00:03:38,733 --> 00:03:39,467
You're scammers!

79
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,000
You think you can fool us?

80
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:42,167
Do you have any proof to support
these accusations

81
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,033
against Miss Cruz?

82
00:03:44,467 --> 00:03:46,100
Yes, we do.

83
00:03:46,233 --> 00:03:47,567
It's on my cellphone.

84
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:52,467
The password?

85
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:55,433
There.

86
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:56,767
Those are her messages.

87
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:02,267
<i> From Miss H...</i>

88
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,467
<i> "Let's meet,</i>

89
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:05,233
I have a job for you."

90
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:13,633
Wait.

91
00:04:13,767 --> 00:04:16,333
That's not substantial evidence.

92
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:18,700
Anyone can type
the name "Miss H."

93
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:21,233
Anyone can claim that number.

94
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:22,267
That is her number.

95
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,300
We can prove it.

96
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:24,200
Go on, call it.

97
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:25,467
Call her.

98
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,333
There, Miss H.

99
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:36,967
There.

100
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:38,767
It's ringing.

101
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:57,133
Dad, I'll just open the gate.

102
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,800
Dad, welcome home!

103
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,000
<i> I'm here, Felma.</i>

104
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,900
<i> I'm home again, my love.</i>

105
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:19,000
Dad, welcome home!

106
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:26,767
Oh my god! Sir Manuel,
is that really you?

107
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:28,067
- Dad!
- Welcome back...

108
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,200
My children.

109
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,033
Ah!

110
00:05:32,167 --> 00:05:33,900
Can I get a turn, too?

111
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,400
Where's Felma?

112
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:39,433
Sir Manuel, you've lost weight.

113
00:05:39,567 --> 00:05:41,067
Where is she?

114
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:47,333
Dad!

115
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:49,033
How did you get here?

116
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:51,733
Did Hazel allow you?

117
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:53,433
One at a time.

118
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:55,667
He's by himself
and can't keep up.

119
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,733
Dad...

120
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:01,067
are you back for good?

121
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:05,200
Aren't you mad at me anymore?

122
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,900
There's the proof
you were looking for.

123
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:18,900
Mrs. Cruz, that ringing phone
is yours, isn't it?

124
00:06:32,867 --> 00:06:34,500
My friend is calling.

125
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:39,267
I'll just answer, just a moment.

126
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,667
Excuse me.

127
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:46,133
Hello, Alice.

128
00:06:46,267 --> 00:06:48,033
Could you call back later?

129
00:06:48,167 --> 00:06:51,067
I'm a bit busy proving
my innocence.

130
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:58,333
What?

131
00:06:58,467 --> 00:06:59,467
Huh?

132
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,600
I'm sure you believe
I have nothing to do

133
00:07:02,733 --> 00:07:05,000
with what these people
are saying.

134
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:07,400
Her husband, Manuel.

135
00:07:08,267 --> 00:07:10,767
He's the one who can prove that
she was the one giving us orders

136
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,700
and paying us.

137
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:14,900
Can you please stop
making things up?

138
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,733
When Manuel was discharged,

139
00:07:17,867 --> 00:07:19,700
a hospital consent form
was obtained.

140
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:21,533
If you like, you can ask
the hospital yourself.

141
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,533
If you have no more questions
for my client,

142
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:28,900
we'll be leaving.

143
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:30,467
Mrs. Cruz?

144
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,067
You two had better
watch yourselves.

145
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,267
You'll both rot in jail.

146
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:49,767
Dad and I proved that Mom and
Dad's suspicions were right.

147
00:07:49,933 --> 00:07:51,833
That Hazel has been deceiving us
for a long time.

148
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,333
She paid Timo to insist

149
00:07:54,467 --> 00:07:56,200
that you were the one
who pushed Jessica.

150
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:57,767
That crazy woman!

151
00:07:58,867 --> 00:08:02,500
Hazel pretended she was helping
to clear your name.

152
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:06,400
But in truth, she paid Timo
to retract his statement.

153
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:11,600
So basically, Hazel paid Timo
twice to lie.

154
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:15,533
And in exchange, Uncle Manuel
would go back to her.

155
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:19,367
That woman is so evil.

156
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:23,633
That's why Dad left.

157
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:26,033
And Mom agreed,
all for you, Coleen.

158
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:30,967
But Dad...

159
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:36,100
why did you let me believe you
were angry at me?

160
00:08:39,067 --> 00:08:40,600
Dear...

161
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:44,633
so you wouldn't carry the guilt
of thinking you were at fault.

162
00:08:44,767 --> 00:08:46,800
But your brother Jeffrey
was right.

163
00:08:46,933 --> 00:08:50,067
There are things you're not
ready to understand yet.

164
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:52,900
I'm sorry, dear, huh?

165
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:55,800
Dad, you didn't
do anything wrong.

166
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:02,133
You even sacrificed
yourself for me.

167
00:09:04,033 --> 00:09:06,000
You endured being
with that woman

168
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:07,933
just so I wouldn't go to prison.

169
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:11,133
So thank you, Dad.

170
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,133
Because of you, I'm free now.

171
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:36,567
There, Felma, go inside.

172
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:39,367
Welcome to Davao, Ma'am Felma.

173
00:09:41,567 --> 00:09:42,733
There.

174
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:47,333
He's always telling me
about you.

175
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:49,167
Come on, Miss Lucy.

176
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:54,133
I hope he only said good things.

177
00:09:54,267 --> 00:09:56,133
He said you're beautiful.

178
00:09:56,267 --> 00:09:58,000
Looks like he was right.

179
00:09:58,133 --> 00:09:59,600
Oh?

180
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:03,833
- Did I really say that?
- Come on, let's eat.

181
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,400
- All right.
- Noah, I prepared

182
00:10:05,533 --> 00:10:06,333
your favorite.

183
00:10:06,467 --> 00:10:07,333
- Really?
- Yes.

184
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:09,567
Yes, I hope
you like it too, Felma.

185
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:11,267
- Come on.
- I hope you like it too

186
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,900
Come on, let's go.

187
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:22,600
There, oh.

188
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:24,500
No, this isn't enough.

189
00:10:24,633 --> 00:10:27,867
Good thing Dad finally
learned the truth.

190
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,533
Otherwise, Hazel would still
have control over him.

191
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:32,533
That woman is pure evil.

192
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:33,600
A child of Satan.

193
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:36,833
Our family has been through
so much.

194
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:40,133
Coleen was jailed and charged.

195
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:43,800
And it was all fabricated
by that woman!

196
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:45,900
Andrea, calm down. ...

197
00:10:46,033 --> 00:10:47,400
Your heart might stop
beating for me.

198
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:49,800
- Hey!
- Ah...

199
00:10:49,933 --> 00:10:52,067
- Oh, no, no.
- I'm right here, bro.

200
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,533
Don't eat here.

201
00:10:53,667 --> 00:10:56,167
Let's just focus on the fact
that we brought Dad home.

202
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:59,200
And Hazel can't do anything
anymore to take him back.

203
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,067
You know,
I've been here a while,

204
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,133
but your mom
still hasn't arrived.

205
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:10,700
Jeff, call your mom.

206
00:11:13,767 --> 00:11:15,100
Okay, Dad, just a moment.

207
00:11:20,233 --> 00:11:21,367
Oh, there.

208
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,400
This is one of the things
we're proud of here in Davao.

209
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:25,367
- Thank you, miss.
- Durian coffee.

210
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:26,967
- Durian coffee.
- Didn't you tell me before

211
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,467
that you like durian?

212
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,933
Now try our coffee.

213
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:32,300
It's freshly ground.

214
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:34,200
There's ice cream, too, right?

215
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:36,067
- It's like durian ice cream.
- Yes, there is.

216
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,267
But that one is special.

217
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,400
Try our coffee.

218
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:43,800
- There.
- Oh?

219
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:46,033
- Oh!
- Okay? There.

220
00:11:46,167 --> 00:11:47,667
Thank you.

221
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:50,133
There, all right.

222
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,200
Hello?

223
00:11:58,333 --> 00:11:59,433
<i> Hi, Mom.</i>

224
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:00,833
Where are you?

225
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:03,567
I've been looking for you.

226
00:12:03,933 --> 00:12:05,200
<i> I have good news.</i>

227
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:06,733
Felma, add some of this.

228
00:12:08,533 --> 00:12:10,100
Is that Uncle Noah?

229
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:15,133
Mom, I thought you were just
taking him to the airport?

230
00:12:20,667 --> 00:12:22,667
Mom?

231
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:24,567
Mom, where are you?

232
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:27,533
I'm here in Davao.

233
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:29,167
What?

234
00:12:34,567 --> 00:12:35,967
Mom, what are you doing there?

235
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:40,067
What was the good news
again, son?

236
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,700
Mom, we brought Dad home.

237
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:47,800
Really?

238
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,367
How did that happen?

239
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,633
<i> Mom, it's a long story.</i>

240
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:52,800
But he's looking for you.

241
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:55,367
So how do I tell him
you're in Davao?

242
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:58,833
Sweetheart,
can we talk next time?

243
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:00,900
My head is starting
to hurt again.

244
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:02,367
Okay?

245
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,033
Noah, please.

246
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:05,667
Oh.

247
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:07,000
Please.

248
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,000
Hello, Jeff?

249
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:15,633
Hello, Uncle?

250
00:13:15,767 --> 00:13:17,467
Why are you and Mom together?

251
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:19,633
Oh...

252
00:13:19,767 --> 00:13:21,600
she just needs some time off.

253
00:13:22,767 --> 00:13:25,033
The weather's giving her
a headache.

254
00:13:25,167 --> 00:13:26,800
But, but don't worry,
she's fine.

255
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:29,733
Hello?

256
00:13:29,867 --> 00:13:31,400
Uncle?

257
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:32,700
Uncle?

258
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,433
- Jeff?
- Oh?

259
00:13:37,567 --> 00:13:39,167
Was that your mom?

260
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,833
No.

261
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:43,767
She's not answering.

262
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:45,367
I've been calling her
for a while now.

263
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:47,800
Maybe there's no signal there.

264
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:02,900
Doctor...

265
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:05,067
could it be something else
and not a tumor?

266
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:11,400
Maybe it could still shrink
or be cured?

267
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:16,633
We need more detailed imaging

268
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:18,767
to check this further.

269
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,833
I suggest an MRI.

270
00:14:23,233 --> 00:14:26,900
Cousin, let's do it ASAP.

271
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,033
All right, cousin.

272
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,567
I'll have my assistant schedule
it within today.

273
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:36,033
Yes.

274
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:40,067
Yes, Mir, Please schedule
Miss Felma's MRI ASAP.

275
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,200
This is urgent.

276
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,067
Yes, thank you.

277
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,367
Thank you.

278
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:47,733
Felma...

279
00:14:48,967 --> 00:14:50,067
are you okay?

280
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:54,967
I'm just thinking
about the kids.

281
00:14:56,967 --> 00:15:00,200
Jeffrey and I didn't even get
to talk properly.

282
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,067
They might be
overthinking things.

283
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:09,333
Especially Manuel.

284
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,933
What do they mean by "taking
some time off"?

285
00:15:30,933 --> 00:15:33,600
Mom wasn't even that tired
from work.

286
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:35,933
Auntie Paz and I handle
most of the work anyway.

287
00:15:37,067 --> 00:15:40,000
She even took leave before to
help with your case.

288
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:46,600
And remember how hard it was
for her when Dad left again?

289
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:47,767
She started drinking.

290
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:49,233
She had so much time.

291
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,767
Maybe Mom's just tired of us.

292
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:56,433
So many things have happened
in our family.

293
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,767
She could've told us, right?

294
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:02,267
Not like this, suddenly
finding out she's in Davao,

295
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,100
and with Uncle Noah
of all people.

296
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:11,500
You know, there's really
something off about Mom.

297
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:13,533
This isn't like her.

298
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:17,100
She always tells us
when she's going somewhere.

299
00:16:17,233 --> 00:16:18,967
She always informs us, right?

300
00:16:20,367 --> 00:16:22,833
How are we going to tell Dad?

301
00:16:22,967 --> 00:16:25,633
He's so excited to see Mom
and be with her again.

302
00:16:28,233 --> 00:16:29,733
He's just going to get jealous.

303
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:35,633
What's going on?

304
00:16:39,633 --> 00:16:41,033
What is this?

305
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,000
Hey.

306
00:16:42,133 --> 00:16:43,067
I'm asking you.

307
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,400
Hey, you too.

308
00:16:44,533 --> 00:16:45,367
What...

309
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:47,667
Didang, could you wash
that again?

310
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:49,367
I don't think
I washed it properly.

311
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,300
What happened?

312
00:16:54,933 --> 00:16:57,700
So my call really came
at the perfect time.

313
00:16:57,833 --> 00:16:59,333
Of course.

314
00:16:59,467 --> 00:17:01,733
That was the evidence
that saved me.

315
00:17:01,867 --> 00:17:03,367
They didn't even think
about it.

316
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:07,067
Of course, I'd use a different
phone to contact them.

317
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:44,967
<i>Kenjie, how was the task
I gave you?</i>

318
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,733
Did your lawyer
actually believe you?

319
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:50,067
Of course.

320
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,700
I fooled them all.

321
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:55,067
What matters is that
I'm safe with Manuel.

322
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:57,667
And most of all,

323
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:00,567
all his suspicions about me
are at a dead end.

324
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:02,000
Good.

325
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,633
Noah.

326
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,300
Noah, I'm scared.

327
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:22,400
Felma, be strong.

328
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:26,767
What if they find
something worse?

329
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:31,167
Just hold on, be strong.

330
00:19:16,667 --> 00:19:17,800
Here you go, Dad.

331
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:21,333
- Oh... bread.
- Another bread.

332
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:22,833
Dad, have some more.

333
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,400
Didn't you like the food?

334
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:27,433
Of course I did.

335
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:28,933
I missed the way you cook.

336
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:30,767
- Here, Dad.
- Oh.

337
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:34,067
- Just let it be.
- All of you, I missed you.

338
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,333
Really?

339
00:19:35,467 --> 00:19:36,900
Is that true, Sir?

340
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:38,567
Even me?

341
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,500
All right, fine.

342
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:42,933
Of course, I missed you, too.

343
00:19:43,067 --> 00:19:45,100
I even missed your gossiping.

344
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,600
- Oh?
- Is that really how you are?

345
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:54,133
Your mom's taking a long time
getting home.

346
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:55,467
Where is she?

347
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:57,967
Have you talked to her, Jeff?

348
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:59,000
What did she say?

349
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:02,800
Well, oh...

350
00:20:02,933 --> 00:20:03,933
What, ah...

351
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:06,433
Dad, I talked to her already.

352
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,000
She said she can't come home yet

353
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:12,633
because she has a conference
in Batangas.

354
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,300
A conference?
What kind of conference?

355
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:20,500
Ah... about the marketing?

356
00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:21,967
Something about marketing.

357
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,067
Marketing?

358
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,467
Shouldn't you be there, too?

359
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:27,200
You're the marketing manager.

360
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:31,400
Mom said...

361
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:34,033
she and Aunt Paz will handle it.

362
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:35,967
Oh.

363
00:20:36,133 --> 00:20:37,600
When is she coming home then?

364
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:41,733
The conference is three days.

365
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:42,900
Four to five days.

366
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:45,567
- Yes, around that.
- Four to five.

367
00:20:46,233 --> 00:20:47,533
Which is it?

368
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:51,400
Didang, eat some more.

369
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:53,233
You sliced that earlier.

370
00:21:00,700 --> 00:21:01,767
Manuel?

371
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:07,000
Manuel, I'm here.

372
00:21:07,133 --> 00:21:09,033
I bought your favorite dessert.

373
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,467
Manuel.

374
00:21:16,133 --> 00:21:17,133
Manuel, the dessert...

375
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,633
Manuel?!

376
00:21:25,467 --> 00:21:27,100
Manuel!

377
00:21:27,233 --> 00:21:28,367
Where are you?

378
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:32,700
Manuel!

379
00:21:34,767 --> 00:21:35,933
Manuel!

380
00:21:38,167 --> 00:21:40,400
So Auntie Felma's on vacation,

381
00:21:40,533 --> 00:21:42,333
and Uncle Noah
is the only one with her?

382
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:44,533
Dad might hear you.

383
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:46,700
Keep your voice down.

384
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:57,767
What are you whispering about?

385
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,333
Ah...

386
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:03,167
About when Andrea will finally
allow suitors.

387
00:22:05,933 --> 00:22:08,367
You're so funny.

388
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:11,467
Andeng, maybe you can
call your mom.

389
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,900
I just want to talk to her.

390
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:17,667
Dad, she's at a conference.

391
00:22:17,833 --> 00:22:19,867
We can't call her.

392
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,900
It'll just be a moment.

393
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:23,000
Come on.

394
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,067
I miss your mom.

395
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,500
Manuel!

396
00:22:26,633 --> 00:22:27,600
Manuel, I know you're there!

397
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:30,233
Felma!
Bring my husband out!

398
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:35,367
Manuel, come on!

399
00:22:36,367 --> 00:22:37,300
Felma!

400
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:38,933
You think I don't know
my husband is there?

401
00:22:39,067 --> 00:22:40,267
He's there!

402
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:41,433
Manuel, come out now!

403
00:22:41,567 --> 00:22:42,933
Come out!

404
00:22:43,933 --> 00:22:44,967
Manuel!

405
00:22:45,767 --> 00:22:47,233
Manuel!

406
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:47,967
Open this door!

407
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:48,933
I know Manuel is in there!

408
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:50,633
Bring my husband out!

409
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:52,367
He's my husband!

410
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:53,867
Manuel!

411
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:55,300
You! Open this door!

412
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,167
- What's your problem?
- Open it!

413
00:22:58,300 --> 00:22:59,767
- Go ahead, oh!
- You have some nerve!

414
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:01,133
You snatched
your father away again!

415
00:23:01,267 --> 00:23:02,567
You never learn!

416
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:03,633
We had an agreement!

417
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:04,733
Manuel!

418
00:23:04,867 --> 00:23:07,433
- You're not allowed...
- Your agreement is over.

419
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:09,033
We already know the truth.

420
00:23:09,167 --> 00:23:10,733
You just kept manipulating us.

421
00:23:10,867 --> 00:23:12,767
But you won't fool us anymore.

422
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:14,400
I don't care about you.

423
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:15,433
I'm only here for my husband!

424
00:23:15,567 --> 00:23:17,567
You're not allowed here!

425
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:18,400
Just a moment!

426
00:23:18,533 --> 00:23:19,567
Let go of me!

427
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:20,667
Wait, he's not even here!

428
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:22,533
You, too!

429
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:24,467
- Hey!
- What?

430
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:26,333
Let go of me!

431
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:27,667
Manuel!

432
00:23:30,133 --> 00:23:31,033
- Stop it!
- Hazel!

433
00:23:31,167 --> 00:23:32,533
That's enough!

434
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:39,500
Don't you ever hurt my children!

435
00:23:39,633 --> 00:23:41,900
I hope your mother
comes home soon.

436
00:23:42,033 --> 00:23:44,533
She'd be so happy to see this.

437
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:49,300
Based on the MRI results
emailed to us,

438
00:23:49,433 --> 00:23:53,333
Dr. Dionela's initial diagnosis
is confirmed.

439
00:23:53,467 --> 00:23:57,133
Meningioma of the frontal lobe
of the brain...

440
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:59,700
A brain tumor.

441
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:05,633
My God, please heal me
for my family.

442
00:24:05,767 --> 00:24:07,833
Please help me.
